<br>
In HoHB, it is impossible to clear the way from point A to point B without the cooperation of multiple groups.  Giggit was not invited to be part of this cooperation.  He was not asked to leave the zone (at least not until he had reached the point where he could not go back to the zone line safely on his own and would need to gate or hammer out); rather, he was simply asked to leave the area where the raid was at the time.  This is not an unreasonable request, especially since a person not involved in the battle strategy communicated across the raid channel is bound to do something to compromise the success of the raid.  Nanur, do you actually expect the raid to first send its instructions to the raid members, then /ooc the instructions to people outside the raid who are just shadowing the raid because they can't get from point A to point B on their own?  Do you honestly think that even if the raid instructions were communicated via /ooc to accommodate uninvited guests, that the instructions would be followed?  After all, Giggit hadn't followed the hundreds (literally) of pleas to leave the vicinity of the raid.<br>
<br>
So of course, when it came time for the final battle, Giggit's stubborn refusal to leave the area was the direct and indisputable cause of the wipe.  Everyone on the raid knew to keep the corner clear so the main tank could pull the mob back to it, and Giggit's refusal to do so kept the tank from being able to keep the mob pointed away from the rest of the raid.<br>
<br>
Giggit singlehandedly and purposefully wasted over 3 hours each for 72 people.  That's 216 hours by my count, just because this dipshit decided he wanted to tag along uninvited and see a raid he was incapable of seeing any other way besides leeching off of the work that 72 other people had done.  And incidentally, he did train see invis mobs to the HoHB zone line after the wipe, further complicating the recovery efforts. <br>
<br>
Oh, and Giggit, the reason Thamgara was accepted into the app guild and you weren't had nothing to do with her being my wife, nor did it have anything to do with the number of knights already in the guild.  It had everything to do with you being a self-absorbed, insensitive, utterly moronic, dateless, virgin-for-life loaf of steaming dog @#%$ and everyone in Triune knowing it.  If Triune had only one member in it, any member, and was reduced to OOCing for &quot;10 peepz to build a phat guild&quot; in PoK, you still wouldn't get in.  And I'd wager that goes the same for any other mid-to-high end guild on MT at this point.<br>
